on the subject. The class $c(\\Omega)$\nis defined using the connection $\\nabla_B$ but it is independent of choice of\nconnection. The class $c(\\Omega)$ is non-trivial and it is zero iff $\\Omega$\nhas a flat algebraic connection and it refines the first Chern class\n$c_1(\\Omega)$ in deRham cohomology and Lie-Rinehart cohomology.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 14 Aug 2012 08:29:28 GMT"},{"version":"v10","created":"Wed, 14 Sep 2022 12:03:27 GMT"},{"version":"v11","created":"Thu, 15 Sep 2022 11:43:48 GMT"},{"version":"v12","created":"Wed, 21 Sep 2022 13:21:36 GMT"},{"version":"v13","created":"Sat, 8 Apr 2023 18:04:36 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 4 Sep 2012 14:00:31 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 18 Sep 2012 13:35:27 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 24 Sep 2012 09:02:30 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Wed, 3 Oct 2012 08:58:32 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Fri, 19 Oct 2012 09:26:41 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Thu, 15 Nov 2012 12:30:25 GMT"},{"version":"v8","created":"Thu, 29 Nov 2012 10:15:18 GMT"},{"version":"v9","created":"Thu, 12 Nov 2020 12:36:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-11"}
